commit.message: Add-back the valgrind suppressions stripped in a bad rebase for prev commit

Potential fix for issue #48

The verifier would only check one macaroon for any given set with the
same third party caveat ID.  This led to the following problems:
 - The verifier would be incomplete, rejecting valid/authorized
   macaroons.
 - There was a potential timing channel in that the evaluation of the
   tree depended upon the order in which the macaroons are passed to the
   verify function.
Distribute valgrind suppressions.
Support FreeBSD make
Add valgrind coverage of unit tests

Disable JSON support by default.

It's not ready, particularly with regard to deciding how to serialize binary
strings or deal with unicode characters.

This must be addressed before it will be enabled.

It can be experimented with by passing
--enable-json-support-that-is-not-production-ready to ./configure.
Add JSON deserialization.
Add JSON serialization
Remove extra EOS from format

Compatibility with Ubuntu 14.04

Added some configure checks, lifted some declarations, fixed Cython, and updated
the README to reflect the newest instructions.
